


02-14-2023 - Conditional Statements More


if-else statements
-if else statements in Java can be used to control the flow the program. Usually, there are multiple blocks of code that will probably be executed based on a condition.


SYNTAX:
if(condition1){
	// this block will be executed in case condition1 is true
}
else if(condition2){
	// this block will be executed in case condition2 is true
}
else{ // any other possibility
	
}



NOTE: If you have only one code statement in an if statement, then you may not use curly braces

SHORT IF-ELSE Statement


if(conditon){
	System.out.println(true);
}
else{
	System.out.println(false);
}



if(conditon) System.out.println(true);
else System.out.println(false);





if(conditon) System.out.println(true);
else{
	System.out.println(false);
	System.out.println("Hello");
}




if(conditon)
	System.out
	.println(true);

else{
	if(condition) System.out.println(false);
	else{
		System.out.println(false);
		System.out.println("Hello");
	}
}

